Recommendation
We recommended and Management agreed to:
Require all officials and employees to liquidate their cash advances immediately and institute appropriate legal sanctions against concerned officials or employees by withholding or suspension of their salaries;
File Request for Write-off those Advances to Officers and Employees which liquidation is no longer possible such that those of the deceased officials and employees and those separated officials after verification, analysis, and validation;
Stop the granting of cash advances to officers and employees who still have unliquidated cash advances and require the attachment of Accountant’s certification in the disbursement for cash advance; and
Strictly implement that all cash advances granted within the year should be liquidated at yearend.

We recommended the Management to:

Follow strictly the regulation in the utilization of the 30% Quick Response Fund (QRF) of the 5% LDRRM Fund as provided in the DBM and DILG Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-1 dated March 25, 2013;

Direct the MDRRM Officer to validate the activities that shall be funded from the 30% QRF and 70% Mitigation Fund according to the four thematic areas for disaster risk reduction and management such as Disaster Prevention and Mitigation, Disaster Preparedness, Disaster Response, and Disaster Rehabilitation and Recovery;

Direct the Municipal Budget Officer and the Municipal Accountant to exercise prudence before proceeding to making any charges and disbursements from the LDRRMF and strictly adhere to related rules and guidelines set out for the allocation and utilization of the LDRRMF; and

Require the MDRRM Officer to furnish the respective Regional DRRM Council and National DRRM Council a copy of the Sanggunian Resolution on every local declaration of State of Calamity pursuant to Section 4 (a) of the NDRRMC Memorandum Order No. 60, s. 2019 and require the Accountant to attach it to the disbursements related to the calamity declared.
